dataIdInfo.idAbs:
The Master Plan of Highways was originally developed by the County of Los Angeles Department of Public Works (DPW); it designates roadways in Los Angeles County by their planned capacity. Categories include major highway, secondary highway, limited secondary highway, parkway, and expressway

UPDATE HISTORY:

  • 12/27/12 - for latest updates reflected in the Santa Clarita Valley Area Plan--went into effect on this day.

  • 6/17/15 - for latest updated reflected in the Antelope Valley Area Plan, adopted by the Board of Supervisors on 6/15/15.
